                  <summary>Remains of a customs pass for wine exportation.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">3 lines of text.</note>
                     <note type="general">This text is one of a group of at least 15 customs documents originating from various individuals and directed to the quintanensis, Andouros.</note>
                     <note type="general">Andouros appears as the recipient of similar orders coming from Sosibios and Rhobaos, also discovered at Berenike.</note>
                     <note type="general">The image associated with this record depicts only one of the sherds making up the ostracon, showing the leftmost remains of the text.</note>
                     <note type="general">The translation below corresponds to the entire text over both fragments.</note>
